df <- as.data.frame(na.omit(example_quantile))\ncheckmate::assert_number(length(class(example_quantile_df)))\n\n# pre-computed scores\nscores_quantile <- score(example_quantile)\nscores_sample_continuous <- score(example_sample_continuous)\nscores_sample_discrete <- score(example_sample_discrete)\nscores_point <- score(example_point)\nscores_binary <- score(example_binary)\nscores_nominal <- score(example_nominal)\n```\n\n**Note:** No `helper-*.R` files found. Setup happens directly in `setup.R`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Example Datasets Used in Tests\n\nThe package uses the following example datasets (all appear to be built-in package data):\n- `example_quantile` - Quantile forecast data\n- `example_binary` - Binary forecast data\n- `example_point` - Point forecast data\n- `example_sample_continuous` - Continuous sample forecast data\n- `example_sample_discrete` - Discrete sample forecast data\n- `example_nominal` - Nominal forecast data\n- `example_quantile_df` - Data frame version of example_quantile (created in setup)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Representative Test Patterns\n\n#### Pattern 1: Testing object creation and validation (test-class-forecast.R)\n\n```r\ntest_that(\"is_forecast() works as expected\", {\n  expect_true(is_forecast(example_binary))\n  expect_true(is_forecast(example_point))\n  expect_true(is_forecast(example_quantile))\n  expect_true(is_forecast(example_sample_continuous))\n  expect_true(is_forecast(example_nominal))\n  \n  expect_false(is_forecast(1:10))\n  expect_false(is_forecast(data.table::as.data.table(example_point)))\n})\n\ntest_that(\"assert_forecast() works as expected\", {\n  expect_error(\n    assert_forecast(data.frame(x = 1:10)),\n    \"The input needs to be a valid forecast object.\"\n  )\n})\n```\n\n#### Pattern 2: Testing metrics computation (test-metrics-binary.R)\n\n```r\ntest_that(\"Binary metrics work within and outside of `score()`\", {\n  result <- score(as_forecast_binary(df))\n  expect_equal(\n    brier_score(observed, predicted),\n 